How Princess Eugenie Broke Royal Tradition With Her Second Wedding Dress|http://www.elle.com/fashion|http://www.elle.com/fashion/a23763696/second-wedding-dress-broke-tradition-princess-eugenie-wedding/||2018-10-14|Ariana Yaptangco||Princess Eugenie wowed with photos of her second wedding dress yesterday, after the Duke of York unveiled a shot of her and husband Jack Brooksbank arriving to their private reception. The royal looked radiant in a flowing Zac Posen gown that broke a royal tradition.

Advertisement - Continue Reading Below

According to Mail Online, Eugenie went against royal brides before her by opting for a blush color. Kate Middleton and Meghan Markle both wore white for their second bridal looks.

Getty Images

Getty Images

Eugenie also shook things up by choosing an American designer instead of a British one. Meghan wore Stella McCartney and Kate chose Alexander McQueen, but Eugenie went with Zac Posen. Posen expressed his delight in an Instagram post writing, &quot;It was an incredible honor to create this dress for HRH Princess Eugenie on her wedding day. Her grace, elegance and strength perfectly embody everything I could hope for in a woman wearing our design.‚Äù


